A Space shutle, when it stands on the launching pad, has a mass of 2.0 x 10(power6) kg. The upward thrust needed to move the shuttle is 3.0 x 10(power 7) N, which is achieved by burning 3.0 xl0(power3) kg of fuel per second and expelling the hot gas thus produced, through the nozzle at the bottom. The, force of upward thrust 1s given by the product of the rate (M) at which fuel is burnt and the exhaust velocity ( u) of the gas relative to the shuttle.
(i) Show that the product, Mu, has the dimensions of torce. (ii) (a) What is the initial acceleralion of the shuttle just as it begins leaving the launching pad ? (b) Assuming that the acccleration of the shuttle is constant, determine the velocity of the shuttle 30s after takeoff.
